articles.title: Temsilcilerimizin rakipleri belli oluyor - TrtSpor
articles.description: Adana Demirspor, Beşiktaş, and Fenerbahçe have learned their opponents for the second qualifying round of the UEFA Europa Conference League. Adana Demirspor will face Romania's CFR Cluj, while Beşiktaş and Fenerbahçe will face the winners of the Tirana-Dinamo Batumi and La Fiorita-Zimbru matches, respectively. The first matches will be played on July 27th, with the second leg on August 3rd. The teams that advance from the second and third qualifying rounds, as well as the play-off round, will qualify for the group stage, which begins on September 21st.

articles.author: Milliyet
articles.title: Ticaret Bakanlığı açıkladı! 6 ay 6 bin kilometre kısıtlaması süresi uzatıldı - Milliyet
articles.description: The Turkish Ministry of Commerce has extended the "6 Months 6,000 Kilometers" restriction until January 1, 2024, to combat excessive and unfair pricing, hoarding, and other unfair commercial practices in the automotive sector. The ministry will also monitor all individual sales subject to the restriction and impose administrative fines on sellers who violate the regulations. Additionally, measures will be taken to eliminate high prices in second-hand vehicle advertisements on the internet. The ministry will continue to conduct rigorous inspections of authorized dealers, auto galleries, and individual sellers to prevent excessive pricing and hoarding. The ministry has imposed a total of 75,171,360 TL in administrative fines for unfair pricing practices.

articles.description: The Central Banks have announced their decisions in the global markets. The Turkish Central Bank will announce its interest rate decision tomorrow. Economists predict that the one-week repo auction interest rate (policy rate) will be increased by 1.075 basis points to 19.25%. According to a survey conducted by AA Finance, the median expectation of economists for the policy rate change was an increase of 1.075 basis points. The new president of the Central Bank, Hafize Gaye Erkan, will lead her first Monetary Policy Committee meeting.

articles.title: Son Dakika: Fenerbahçe, Edin Dzeko transferini bitiriyor! 48 saat içinde... - Hürriyet
articles.description: Fenerbahçe is close to signing Edin Dzeko from Inter Milan, according to reports. The Bosnian striker's agent was said to be in Istanbul to discuss the final details of the deal, which is expected to be completed within 48 hours. Dzeko, 37, is reportedly set to earn €4.5m per year plus a €1m bonus, as well as a signing-on fee of around €5m.

articles.description: This article discusses the upcoming retirement and salary increases for Turkish civil servants and retirees. The minimum wage will increase to 11,402 lira as of July 1st, and the retirement and salary increases will be determined based on inflation rates and a welfare increase. The exact amount of the increase will be announced after the inflation rates for June are released by TÜİK after the Eid al-Adha holiday. The new salaries will be determined based on a combination of inflation rates, welfare increases, and gradual salary increases.

articles.description: This article reports that Sweden has finally approved a law that imposes prison sentences on supporters of terrorist organizations. The law, which came into effect on June 1, allows for up to four years in prison for those who encourage, strengthen, or support terrorist activities. The law was used for the first time against a person accused of supporting the PKK, a Kurdish militant group. The accused, who was arrested in January after firing a gun outside a restaurant in Stockholm, is alleged to have attempted to finance the group through extortion. The law also expands the powers of authorities to detain and prosecute those who finance or support terrorist organizations.

articles.author: Haber Global
articles.title: Düzenli aspirin kullananlar, anemi tehdidiyle karşı karşıya - Haber Global
articles.description: Regular use of aspirin can lead to anemia in people aged 65 and over, according to a study of more than 18,000 people in Australia and the US. The study found a link between the use of aspirin in the non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug group and anemia. Participants were observed for five years, with half taking 100mg of aspirin a day and the other half taking a placebo. Doctors regularly checked the levels of the ferritin protein and hemoglobin in their blood cells. The study found that those taking aspirin had lower levels of hemoglobin and ferritin, and a 20% higher risk of developing anemia than those not taking aspirin.
